Three motorists were robbed at gunpoint after driving over objects which damaged their vehicles. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng police officials are warning motorists to be aware of armed robbers along the N1 highway in Johannesburg.They have confirmed there have been three incidents at the Buccleuch interchange in Sandton recently.Three motorists were robbed at gunpoint after driving over objects which damaged their vehicles.The police's David Mothapo said, Victims will see things rolling onto the road, the car will break down and they will stop to try and fix it. While checking the problem, suspects will appear and start robbing you. 